														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-795222">
									

<p>I can understand why someone would not associate 682 with this, because this paints a picture of 682's true nature that doesn't mesh with its Kill EVERYthing motives. This makes it out to be a happy go lucky social creature with a previous life that we can relate to and it is lashing out only because of pain and fear.</p>
<p>I'm not saying this is a bad story, the entire point is that you aren't supposed to expect whose perspective you are reading from until you get to the end, but I think that the "real" 682 is so alien that its pre-containment existence is some Lovecraftian unknowable and that it can't possibly relate to us in anyway.</p>

							</div>

								
					
